Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteFPObject(25.10)                                    deleteFPObject(25.10)

Name
       deleteFPObject - Deletes the specified floorplan object by name

Syntax
        deleteFPObject

       [-help]

       objectType

       objectName

       Deletes the specified floorplan object by name. You can use the command
       at any point in the design flow.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deleteFPObject parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteFPObject

       <objectName>
              Specifies the name of the object for the  <objectType>.  To  get
              <objectName>, you can use <dbObjToName objPtr> where <objPtr> is
              the target object db pointer.

              Data_type: string, required

       <objectType>
              Specifies  the  type  of object for the <objectName>. The object
              type can be any of the following:

              * Placement Blockage (LayerShape)

              * Partial Placement Blockage (LayerShape)

              * Routing Blockage (LayerShape)

              * Partition Feedthrough (PtnFeed)

              * Partition Pin Blockage (PtnPinBlk)

              Data_type: string, required

Examples
              *

                The  following  command   deletes   the   placement   blockage
                (658300,824180,874060,1048640) from the current design:

                deleteFPObject LayerShape (658300,824180,874060,1048640)

                Note: You can get  "objectName" by using [dbObjToName objPtr],
                where  objPtr  is the db pointer to the placement blockage ob-
                ject.

                This is similar to,

                deleteFPobject LayerShape [dbObjToName objPtr]

              * The following command deletes the Partial  Placement  Blockage
                from the current design:

                deleteFPObject LayerShape (1079960,1006880,1211620,1111280)

              * The  following  command  deletes the Routing Blockage from the
                current design:

                deleteFPObject LayerShape (628350,905550,857290,1057010)

              * The following command deletes the Partition  Feedthrough  from
                the current design:

                deleteFPObject PtnFeed (980200,912920,1298040,954140)

              * The  following  command delete Partition Pin Blockage from the
                current design:

                deleteFPObject PtnPinBlk (970780,947630,1007150,1012280)

Related Information
              * dbObjToName

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

